<i>♪ But my jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

871
01:02:35.800 --> 01:02:39.840
<i>♪ Come all</i>
<i>ye pretty fair maids ♪</i>

872
01:02:40.320 --> 01:02:43.880
<i>♪ Whoever you may be ♪</i>

873
01:02:44.160 --> 01:02:48.080
<i>♪ Who love</i>
<i>a jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

874
01:02:48.360 --> 01:02:51.560
<i>♪ That plow</i>
<i>the raging sea ♪</i>

875
01:02:52.880 --> 01:02:56.960
<i>♪ My heart is</i>
<i>pierced by Cupid ♪</i>

876
01:02:57.040 --> 01:03:01.080
<i>♪ I disdain</i>
<i>all glittering gold ♪</i>

877
01:03:01.360 --> 01:03:05.120
<i>♪ There is nothing</i>
<i>can console me ♪</i>

878
01:03:05.960 --> 01:03:09.600
<i>♪ But my jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

879
01:03:10.960 --> 01:03:14.720
<i>♪ My heart</i>
<i>is pierced by Cupid ♪</i>

880
01:03:15.120 --> 01:03:19.000
<i>♪ I disdain</i>
<i>all glittering gold ♪</i>

881
01:03:19.120 --> 01:03:23.160
<i>♪ There is nothing</i>
<i>can console me ♪</i>

882
01:03:23.280 --> 01:03:27.640
<i>♪ But my jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

883
01:03:32.920 --> 01:03:36.320
[hissing]
[muffled scream]

884
01:03:36.400 --> 01:03:37.640
[shrieks]

885
01:03:37.760 --> 01:03:41.040
[grunts]
[men shouting]

886
01:03:46.600 --> 01:03:48.920
[shrieking]
[shouting]

887
01:03:51.920 --> 01:03:53.720
[shouting]

888
01:03:58.840 --> 01:04:00.600
[shrieking]

889
01:04:02.480 --> 01:04:06.240
[men shouting]
Out upon it! It has begun!

890
01:04:09.280 --> 01:04:10.600
[all grunting]

891
01:04:10.720 --> 01:04:14.280
[shouting]
[mermaids hissing]

892
01:04:16.160 --> 01:04:17.080
[men screaming]

893
01:04:24.600 --> 01:04:26.720
[shrieking]
[gasps]

894
01:04:27.280 --> 01:04:28.920
[screaming]

895
01:04:36.480 --> 01:04:38.200
[shrieking continues]

896
01:04:39.560 --> 01:04:42.120
[indistinct screaming]

897
01:04:43.640 --> 01:04:45.880
[gurgling]

898
01:04:48.400 --> 01:04:49.920
Light 'em up!

899
01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:54.720
Muster your courage!
Drive 'em to shore!

900
01:04:58.800 --> 01:05:01.560
[grunts]
[mermaid screams]

901
01:05:04.880 --> 01:05:08.440
Nets into the water!
Quickly!

902
01:05:08.720 --> 01:05:10.280
[shrieking continues]

903
01:05:11.440 --> 01:05:13.320
[all shouting]

904
01:05:21.640 --> 01:05:22.760
[sword vibrates]

905
01:05:27.560 --> 01:05:29.680
[mermaids shrieking]

906
01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:47.320
[net whips]

907
01:05:47.400 --> 01:05:49.040
[whipping continues]
[grunting]

908
01:05:49.120 --> 01:05:51.160
[men screaming]

909
01:05:53.400 --> 01:05:55.800
[shrieks]
[screams]

910
01:05:55.880 --> 01:05:58.080
[all shouting]

911
01:05:58.200 --> 01:06:01.080
Retreat, all, to land!
For your lives!

912
01:06:01.600 --> 01:06:03.680
[shrieks and screams continue]

913
01:06:04.600 --> 01:06:05.960
Retreat, I say!

914
01:06:06.040 --> 01:06:08.520
Cowards! Back in the water!

915
01:06:08.640 --> 01:06:12.520
There be no refuge on land!
On my word!

916
01:06:13.200 --> 01:06:14.160
[yelps]

917
01:06:16.760 --> 01:06:19.520
[shrieks of
approaching mermaids]

918
01:06:33.400 --> 01:06:34.320
[gasps]

919
01:06:34.400 --> 01:06:37.040
[hissing]
[gasps]

920
01:06:45.760 --> 01:06:47.160
Come on!

921
01:06:47.240 --> 01:06:49.720
[all clamoring]

922
01:06:57.920 --> 01:06:59.840
[shrieks]
[grunts]

923
01:07:05.680 --> 01:07:08.480
[grunts]
[screams]

924
01:07:16.280 --> 01:07:18.080
[breathes heavily]

925
01:07:32.640 --> 01:07:34.160
[grunting]

926
01:07:43.640 --> 01:07:46.520
[faint screaming, shrieking]

927
01:08:06.640 --> 01:08:07.920
[grunts]

928
01:08:13.280 --> 01:08:16.000
[muffled shrieking]

929
01:08:21.760 --> 01:08:23.560
We got one!

930
01:08:28.200 --> 01:08:29.920
I'm in love!

931
01:08:32.040 --> 01:08:33.720
Check the wounded!

932
01:08:34.080 --> 01:08:37.200
See if you can find
one mermaid still alive!

933
01:08:38.080 --> 01:08:39.400
[groans]

934
01:08:40.640 --> 01:08:43.160
[splashing nearby]

935
01:08:57.000 --> 01:08:58.160
[gasps]

936
01:09:03.480 --> 01:09:05.280
[panting]

937
01:09:12.280 --> 01:09:13.600
[hissing]

938
01:09:16.080 --> 01:09:18.520
Come, give a hand!
[hisses]

939
01:09:18.640 --> 01:09:20.520
Well done, sailor.

940
01:09:21.680 --> 01:09:23.200
Did everyone see that?

941
01:09:23.280 --> 01:09:25.440
Because I will not
be doing it again.

942
01:09:25.520 --> 01:09:30.200
Back to the ship. We head
for a protected cove. Now.

943
01:09:30.960 --> 01:09:34.440
[hissing]

944
01:09:46.800 --> 01:09:48.520
[man] Lord. Is that...?

945
01:09:48.600 --> 01:09:50.080
[Gibbs] Mermaid.

946
01:09:50.160 --> 01:09:53.680
Give up this madness now.
I cannot.

947
01:09:54.440 --> 01:09:56.080
Ever walk on the beach,

948
01:09:56.160 --> 01:09:58.120
look back and see your
footsteps in the sand?

949
01:09:58.240 --> 01:10:01.880
It's like that, except
the footsteps lie before me.

950
01:10:02.280 --> 01:10:06.320
Footstep, actually.
Whitecap Bay, sir.

951
01:10:06.400 --> 01:10:08.840
We must hasten.
[shrieking]

952
01:10:12.480 --> 01:10:15.360
[men screaming]

953
01:10:15.920 --> 01:10:19.400
We travel by foot.
Gibbs, I require a heading.

954
01:10:19.640 --> 01:10:22.680
But, sir, the men.
They be dead already.

955
01:10:22.760 --> 01:10:26.200
They don't sound dead.
Oh, is that so?

956
01:10:26.320 --> 01:10:30.080
Well, I hear nothing
but seagulls nesting.

957
01:10:30.480 --> 01:10:32.720
What is it that you hear,
Mr. Groves?

958
01:10:32.840 --> 01:10:34.880
[men continue shrieking]

959
01:10:35.480 --> 01:10:38.200
Seagulls... nesting.

960
01:10:39.080 --> 01:10:42.400
Nothing more.
Heading, Gibbs?

961
01:10:45.480 --> 01:10:49.320
[wood creaking]
[screaming continues]

962
01:10:50.920 --> 01:10:52.760
My God.

963
01:10:52.840 --> 01:10:54.920
[gun cocking]
Your head or my heading.

964
01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:57.080
I'll have me one or t'other,
I don't care which.

965
01:10:57.200 --> 01:10:59.480
[panting]

966
01:11:02.240 --> 01:11:04.560
All hands, forward!

967
01:11:20.200 --> 01:11:24.640
It's to you now, Sparrow.
Was that really necessary?

968
01:11:24.800 --> 01:11:27.280
Best you not know the exact
whereabouts of my ship.

969
01:11:27.360 --> 01:11:31.120
I be a cautious man.
So be I.

970
01:11:32.200 --> 01:11:34.000
What I want first...

971
01:11:34.120 --> 01:11:36.160
[clicking]

972
01:11:37.800 --> 01:11:39.800
...is Ponce De Leon's ship.

973
01:12:10.200 --> 01:12:12.240
[insects chittering]

974
01:12:13.240 --> 01:12:16.400
[birds squawking]

975
01:12:16.760 --> 01:12:18.720
Why is it we've got
to bring her along?

976
01:12:18.840 --> 01:12:21.800
Because tears don't keep.
We need them fresh.

977
01:12:22.120 --> 01:12:23.960
What is the ritual again?

978
01:12:25.000 --> 01:12:27.640
Water from the Fountain
and a mermaid's tear?

979
01:12:27.720 --> 01:12:29.120
And two silver chalices.

980
01:12:29.240 --> 01:12:31.400
One cup with a tear,
one without.

981
01:12:33.160 --> 01:12:35.680
So, one with a tear
and water in both?

982
01:12:35.760 --> 01:12:37.240
Quite complicated,
is it not?

983
01:12:37.320 --> 01:12:40.360
Both get water.
One gets a tear.

984
01:12:40.440 --> 01:12:43.200
The person who drinks
the water with the tear

985
01:12:43.280 --> 01:12:45.880
gets all the years
of life from the other.

986
01:12:47.120 --> 01:12:49.760
How many years? Whoa.

987
01:12:50.640 --> 01:12:53.680
All the years
that they have lived,

988
01:12:53.800 --> 01:12:57.880
and they could have lived,
if fate had been kinder.

989
01:12:57.960 --> 01:12:59.560
[hissing]

990
01:13:06.440 --> 01:13:07.720
Clergyman.

991
01:13:09.600 --> 01:13:12.760
On the off chance that this
does not go well for me,

992
01:13:12.840 --> 01:13:14.600
I would like it noted
here and now

993
01:13:14.680 --> 01:13:17.600
that I am fully prepared
to believe in whatever I must,

994
01:13:17.920 --> 01:13:19.760
so that I may be
welcomed into that place

995
01:13:19.840 --> 01:13:22.240
where all the goody-goodies
get to go. Savvy?

996
01:13:22.320 --> 01:13:26.200
We have
a word for that, Jack.
You can convert.

997
01:13:26.320 --> 01:13:28.560
I was thinking more
of an as-needed basis.

998
01:13:30.240 --> 01:13:31.880
[gasping]

999
01:13:32.800 --> 01:13:34.000
Quartermaster!

1000
01:13:34.400 --> 01:13:36.240
Aye?
She cannot breathe!

1001
01:13:36.320 --> 01:13:39.280
She has water.
She needs air!

1002
01:13:43.480 --> 01:13:45.840
Open this.
She will escape.

1003
01:13:45.920 --> 01:13:49.280
You're killing her.
I support the
missionary's position.

1004
01:13:49.400 --> 01:13:50.800
[laughs]

1005
01:13:50.880 --> 01:13:52.000
[grunts]

1006
01:13:54.080 --> 01:13:55.840
[gasps]

1007
01:13:55.960 --> 01:13:57.360
[panting]

1008
01:13:57.680 --> 01:13:58.840
See?

1009
01:14:04.040 --> 01:14:05.200
Onward.

1010
01:14:29.920 --> 01:14:33.280
Just as I thought.
Not this way!

1011
01:14:35.200 --> 01:14:36.880
This is the way,
isn't it?

1012
01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:39.680
'Course it is,
but we should go
around to the east.

1013
01:14:39.800 --> 01:14:41.920
That would take us out of
the path of the chalices.

1014
01:14:42.040 --> 01:14:44.040
Well, then
we'll circle back.
There is no time.

1015
01:14:44.120 --> 01:14:45.640
You're the one
who insisted on bringing
the bloody mermaid.

1016
01:14:45.720 --> 01:14:47.680
Well, the mutiny
didn't help.
You walk like a girl.

1017
01:14:47.840 --> 01:14:49.920
You would know.
Someone must go.

1018
01:14:50.880 --> 01:14:52.400
You mean split up?

1019
01:14:52.480 --> 01:14:55.280
You mean jump?
This I cannot wait to see.

1020
01:14:55.360 --> 01:14:59.360
Sparrow will go.
Find the ship,
retrieve the chalices.

1021
01:14:59.440 --> 01:15:01.600
Sparrow? What makes you
think he will come back?

1022
01:15:01.680 --> 01:15:05.000
Yes, what makes you think
he will come back?

1023
01:15:05.080 --> 01:15:07.480
We cannot trust him, Father.
I'll go.

1024
01:15:08.400 --> 01:15:09.480
She'll go.

1025
01:15:14.080 --> 01:15:15.800
How much farther
to the Fountain?

1026
01:15:15.920 --> 01:15:17.920
I'm running out of time.

1027
01:15:19.040 --> 01:15:21.760
About a day's march north,
following that river,

1028
01:15:21.840 --> 01:15:24.680
you'll get to
a series of pools.
Then you're close.

1029
01:15:27.680 --> 01:15:29.000
You will go.

1030
01:15:31.400 --> 01:15:33.880
I was sure
it would come to this.

1031
01:15:47.760 --> 01:15:49.640
You know that feeling
you get sometimes

1032
01:15:49.720 --> 01:15:51.800
when you're standing
in a high place?

1033
01:15:52.200 --> 01:15:54.000
Sudden urge to jump?

1034
01:15:55.960 --> 01:15:57.240
I don't have it.

1035
01:15:57.320 --> 01:16:00.560
[gun cocks]
I need those chalices.

1036
01:16:00.680 --> 01:16:03.200
Shoot. Save me
the bother of the fall.

1037
01:16:03.320 --> 01:16:05.720
You will go.
You will return...

1038
01:16:07.480 --> 01:16:09.560
...or I will kill her.

1039
01:16:12.360 --> 01:16:14.080
You won't kill
your own daughter.

1040
01:16:14.160 --> 01:16:16.960
Quartermaster,
get me six more pistols,

1041
01:16:17.040 --> 01:16:18.720
remove the shot
from all but two,

1042
01:16:18.840 --> 01:16:20.680
but do not
tell me which two.

1043
01:16:23.320 --> 01:16:26.160
You get to choose,
Mr. Sparrow.
Oh.

1044
01:16:29.000 --> 01:16:33.280
No. Mmm... No.

1045
01:16:36.320 --> 01:16:39.280
Yes.
You're sure?

1046
01:16:39.360 --> 01:16:40.760
'Course I am.

1047
01:16:45.600 --> 01:16:46.800
[gun clicks]

1048
01:16:49.360 --> 01:16:50.360
Again.

1049
01:16:51.280 --> 01:16:54.320
Please,
they're not even loaded.
[all gasp]

1050
01:16:55.600 --> 01:16:56.720
[all gasp]

1051
01:16:59.360 --> 01:17:00.400
Again.

1052
01:17:01.080 --> 01:17:03.120
If you're so keen
on killing her,

1053
01:17:03.200 --> 01:17:05.720
why don't you just
let her jump?
What?

1054
01:17:05.840 --> 01:17:08.880
Mm-mm!
If you jump and die,

1055
01:17:08.960 --> 01:17:11.520
then she will
have her chance. 

1056
01:17:12.680 --> 01:17:13.960
Again.

1057
01:17:17.440 --> 01:17:22.880
Oi... if I jump,
will I survive?

1058
01:17:25.880 --> 01:17:27.280
The doll.

1059
01:17:30.400 --> 01:17:32.880
[chanting in foreign language]

1060
01:17:36.640 --> 01:17:40.200
[Jack screaming]

1061
01:17:40.320 --> 01:17:41.520
[doll splashes in water]

1062
01:17:43.600 --> 01:17:48.600
Yes, now you will survive.
This is nonsense! I'm going!

1063
01:17:50.560 --> 01:17:54.320
[screaming]

1064
01:18:03.560 --> 01:18:05.280
[gasps]

1065
01:18:07.040 --> 01:18:10.080
Wet. Wet again.

1066
01:18:12.400 --> 01:18:15.840
[Quartermaster] We go on.
Due north to the Fountain.

1067
01:18:16.200 --> 01:18:17.840
Well played, Father.

1068
01:18:19.440 --> 01:18:21.680
You knew which guns
were loaded, right?

1069
01:18:24.360 --> 01:18:25.960
Of course, my love.

1070
01:18:36.080 --> 01:18:38.920
Be nice to have
a map about now.

1071
01:18:39.000 --> 01:18:41.200
Or a ship.
[crickets chittering]

1072
01:18:41.320 --> 01:18:45.360
Stop!
Hold very still.

1073
01:18:46.440 --> 01:18:49.840
Ye dare not let it
touch your skin.

1074
01:18:58.880 --> 01:19:02.080
What? What be wrong with
an older man having a hobby?

1075
01:19:02.160 --> 01:19:05.000
What are you
stopping for, eh?
Push on!

1076
01:19:05.080 --> 01:19:08.240
Push on!
You can sleep
when you're dead. Push on!

1077
01:19:09.920 --> 01:19:13.600
Fortune continues
to favor us.

1078
01:19:41.280 --> 01:19:43.560
The <i>Santiago.</i>

1079
01:19:43.640 --> 01:19:46.160
Famously captained
by Ponce de Leon.

1080
01:19:46.960 --> 01:19:50.240
Oh. There's no one there.

1081
01:19:50.480 --> 01:19:51.520
Right, then.

1082
01:19:51.880 --> 01:19:53.680
[seagulls crying]

1083
01:20:02.320 --> 01:20:04.600
[glass shatters]

1084
01:20:21.120 --> 01:20:23.040
[panting]

1085
01:20:25.840 --> 01:20:27.520
We must not stop.

1086
01:20:29.600 --> 01:20:30.880
[gasps]

1087
01:20:35.560 --> 01:20:36.960
You will walk.

1088
01:20:54.240 --> 01:20:58.200
[grunts] I cannot.

1089
01:20:59.120 --> 01:21:00.480
Walk or die.

1090
01:21:06.880 --> 01:21:08.440
Put your arms around me.

1091
01:21:08.520 --> 01:21:11.760
I do not ask for help.
But you need it.

1092
01:21:29.040 --> 01:21:33.120
We're in a hurry, yes?
Do not fall behind.

1093
01:21:52.400 --> 01:21:54.440
Hold here till I say!

1094
01:22:07.200 --> 01:22:08.800
Such beauty.

1095
01:22:09.680 --> 01:22:12.320
Surely you're one of
God's own creations,

1096
01:22:12.760 --> 01:22:16.000
and not a descendant
of those dark creatures

1097
01:22:16.080 --> 01:22:17.800
who found
no refuge on the Ark.

1098
01:22:20.680 --> 01:22:22.120
Such beauty...

1099
01:22:24.080 --> 01:22:25.840
...and yet deadly.

1100
01:22:26.560 --> 01:22:28.440
Deadly? No.

1101
01:22:28.880 --> 01:22:30.400
You attacked me.

1102
01:22:31.160 --> 01:22:35.400
No. You are different.

1103
01:22:36.240 --> 01:22:37.600
Different?

1104
01:22:37.840 --> 01:22:40.920
Are you not? You protect.

1105
01:22:44.920 --> 01:22:46.120
[mutters] Did you...?

1106
01:22:48.000 --> 01:22:50.120
You pushed me down
out of the way.

1107
01:22:51.560 --> 01:22:56.160
You see the Fountain?
No, but we are close.

1108
01:22:56.720 --> 01:22:58.720
Bring the creature.
Cover its head.

1109
01:22:59.160 --> 01:23:00.720
She has a name!

1110
01:23:05.320 --> 01:23:06.760
Pray tell.

1111
01:23:13.200 --> 01:23:14.640
She is Syrena.

1112
01:23:19.800 --> 01:23:22.000
[grunting]

1113
01:23:43.040 --> 01:23:44.640
[grunts]

1114
01:23:51.960 --> 01:23:55.240
[wood creaking]
[wind whistling]

1115
01:23:55.560 --> 01:23:57.680
Ponce de Leon.

1116
01:24:00.760 --> 01:24:04.960
[Barbossa] If 40 pirates
dreamt 40 nights of treasure,

1117
01:24:05.040 --> 01:24:08.560
it would not match
the contents of this room.

1118
01:24:09.160 --> 01:24:10.240
You.

1119
01:24:12.800 --> 01:24:15.760
You.
No...

1120
01:24:15.840 --> 01:24:18.280
...you.
I was here first.

1121
01:24:18.360 --> 01:24:22.440
You, why are you here?
Blackbeard sent me.

1122
01:24:22.520 --> 01:24:25.080
Why are you?
Silver chalices

1123
01:24:25.160 --> 01:24:28.520
for my royal liege.
Oh, please.

1124
01:24:29.600 --> 01:24:31.920
Back, back! We have
to balance it out!

1125
01:24:33.280 --> 01:24:36.080
The whole ship will slide!

1126
01:24:39.680 --> 01:24:40.880
Right, then.

1127
01:24:41.520 --> 01:24:47.520
What if we each choose
an item of approximately
equal weight?

1128
01:24:50.400 --> 01:24:51.640
Put it back!

1129
01:24:53.120 --> 01:24:54.960
We touch nothing!

1130
01:24:59.400 --> 01:25:02.640
[objects rattling]

1131
01:25:03.160 --> 01:25:04.680
What about that?

1132
01:25:04.840 --> 01:25:06.280
The chalices.

1133
01:25:08.280 --> 01:25:10.440
Oi! Why do you
get to look first?

1134
01:25:10.520 --> 01:25:11.680
Fine, then.

1135
01:25:13.320 --> 01:25:17.200
[ship groaning]
[grunts]

1136
01:25:23.160 --> 01:25:24.160
[grunts]

1137
01:25:30.960 --> 01:25:32.280
[both] Together.

1138
01:25:35.160 --> 01:25:36.240
[Jack] Rocks.

1139
01:25:37.480 --> 01:25:38.760
The Spanish.

1140
01:25:39.480 --> 01:25:41.200
They're ahead of us, mate.

1141
01:25:42.080 --> 01:25:43.720
I shall have
a look at that map.

1142
01:25:44.160 --> 01:25:45.680
If it's what I fear...

1143
01:25:47.920 --> 01:25:49.720
[grunts]

1144
01:25:49.800 --> 01:25:53.120
[mutters indistinctly]
[coin tinkles]

1145
01:25:55.480 --> 01:25:57.360
I wonder why they
left this behind.

1146
01:26:00.960 --> 01:26:04.360
[whispering]
Don't touch the map.

1147
01:26:06.000 --> 01:26:07.160
Oh.

1148
01:26:09.600 --> 01:26:11.160
They know the path,

1149
01:26:11.440 --> 01:26:15.080
but I can also see where
they'll most likely make camp.

1150
01:26:28.440 --> 01:26:30.200
[Gibbs] Jack!
Shh!

1151
01:26:32.880 --> 01:26:36.200
Gibbs, I was just on me way
to break you out of jail.

1152
01:26:36.320 --> 01:26:40.280
Hmm.
You stole my map.

1153
01:26:40.600 --> 01:26:43.440
Oh!
Right. Best be started.

1154
01:26:46.560 --> 01:26:47.720
Ole.

1155
01:27:05.360 --> 01:27:07.200
[Blackbeard] Mermaids.

1156
01:27:09.600 --> 01:27:12.640
Careful, these pools run deep.

1157
01:27:12.720 --> 01:27:16.440
If she escapes, all is lost.
Quartermaster.

1158
01:27:16.560 --> 01:27:21.600
[hissing]
[Blackbeard] Look. Look!

1159
01:27:22.600 --> 01:27:26.360
Staked out to die,
to dry in the sun.

1160
01:27:26.440 --> 01:27:29.520
Only half in the water.
Not enough to live,

1161
01:27:29.640 --> 01:27:34.040
but just enough to make
the dying slow.

1162
01:27:34.800 --> 01:27:36.280
Think on it.

1163
01:27:36.400 --> 01:27:39.840
Your people, murdered,
harvested for their tears.

1164
01:27:40.240 --> 01:27:44.240
Syrena, won't you cry?

1165
01:27:44.920 --> 01:27:47.000
All die, even you.

1166
01:27:47.120 --> 01:27:50.440
Soon, I hear.
Listen...

1167
01:27:52.080 --> 01:27:54.360
[hisses]
Listen.

1168
01:27:54.440 --> 01:27:58.000
Can you not hear
your sisters scream?

1169
01:27:58.120 --> 01:28:01.200
[faint shrieks]
Do you not hear them?

1170
01:28:01.280 --> 01:28:03.880
We need but one tear.

1171
01:28:05.920 --> 01:28:08.440
[gasps]
Vile creature!

1172
01:28:08.520 --> 01:28:11.200
Chop off her fingers,
one by one!
Choke her!

1173
01:28:11.280 --> 01:28:13.680
[man] Cut out the tears
from behind the eyes!

1174
01:28:14.000 --> 01:28:15.680
Where's your voice in this?

1175
01:28:16.400 --> 01:28:17.920
Maybe she'll have
a change of heart

1176
01:28:18.000 --> 01:28:19.520
when the sun rises.

1177
01:28:19.600 --> 01:28:22.080
Oh, aye,
she will burn,

1178
01:28:22.160 --> 01:28:23.560
but I cannot
wait for the sun.

1179
01:28:23.640 --> 01:28:25.320
Perhaps we should
build a fire.

1180
01:28:25.400 --> 01:28:27.440
No.
Do not contest me, cleric.

1181
01:28:27.520 --> 01:28:30.600
You will not torture her.
We need only one tear.

1182
01:28:30.680 --> 01:28:34.080
I will tear every scale
from her body one by one
if I see fit.

1183
01:28:34.160 --> 01:28:36.040
If that displeases you,
go pray.

1184
01:28:36.120 --> 01:28:39.080
I was wrong. Not every soul
can be saved. Yours cannot.

1185
01:28:39.280 --> 01:28:42.000
Behold, gentlemen,
a man formerly of faith.

1186
01:28:42.080 --> 01:28:43.600
That vile creature,
as you call her,

1187
01:28:43.680 --> 01:28:45.000
is worth
a hundred of you.

1188
01:28:45.080 --> 01:28:46.440
Oh, you care for her?

1189
01:28:49.000 --> 01:28:50.920
You fancy her.

1190
01:28:52.560 --> 01:28:55.920
And do not deny what is
clear to my eyes.

1191
01:28:56.840 --> 01:28:58.280
Question is...

1192
01:29:01.480 --> 01:29:03.400
...does she fancy you?

1193
01:29:05.600 --> 01:29:09.680
By God, she does.
We are in luck!

1194
01:29:10.920 --> 01:29:13.760
Bring forth a tear...

1195
01:29:13.840 --> 01:29:16.560
...or witness the death
of this poor soul.

1196
01:29:16.680 --> 01:29:18.720
[grunts, gasps]
[hisses]

1197
01:29:18.840 --> 01:29:22.200
Syrena, if you could
manage a tear,

1198
01:29:22.280 --> 01:29:23.680
I would be grateful.

1199
01:29:25.080 --> 01:29:27.000
Sadness, yes,

1200
01:29:27.120 --> 01:29:32.520
but no sorrow... yet.
Not by your hand, Father!

1201
01:29:32.680 --> 01:29:35.440
Time and tide wait for none.
Quartermaster.

1202
01:29:36.280 --> 01:29:38.400
[grunt]
[pained cry]

1203
01:29:47.800 --> 01:29:50.560
Ooh, aye,
mermaids are tough.

1204
01:29:51.480 --> 01:29:52.840
The lot of them.

1205
01:29:53.240 --> 01:29:57.240
Tie her up like the others.
And get rid of this.

1206
01:29:57.920 --> 01:29:59.800
[Syrena struggling]

1207
01:30:02.320 --> 01:30:04.640
You are confident?
Yes.

1208
01:30:05.480 --> 01:30:08.440
I am a woman.
So is she.

1209
01:30:11.680 --> 01:30:13.240
[grunting]

1210
01:30:16.160 --> 01:30:19.320
[Gibbs]
What's your play, Jack?
Throwing in with Barbossa.

1211
01:30:20.320 --> 01:30:21.920
There is a girl...

1212
01:30:22.400 --> 01:30:25.680
...a female...
of the opposite sex.

1213
01:30:25.760 --> 01:30:29.600
When is there not?
Perhaps I should
say "damsel."

1214
01:30:29.680 --> 01:30:32.800
You're rescuing a damsel?
Well, there's a first.

1215
01:30:32.880 --> 01:30:36.080
Yes, but it's just that
I may have caused said damsel

1216
01:30:36.200 --> 01:30:37.920
some manner of harm
many moons ago.

1217
01:30:38.000 --> 01:30:39.520
Out with it.

1218
01:30:40.280 --> 01:30:43.640
Gibbs, this is
the woman from Seville.

1219
01:30:43.720 --> 01:30:45.920
Ah, you pretended
to love her,

1220
01:30:46.000 --> 01:30:47.520
then you left her
and broke her heart.

1221
01:30:47.600 --> 01:30:51.960
Worse. I may have had,
briefly, mind you...

1222
01:30:54.480 --> 01:30:57.000
...stirrings.
Stirrings?

1223
01:30:57.680 --> 01:31:01.440
Stirrings.
What? Like feelings,
you mean?

1224
01:31:01.640 --> 01:31:05.000
No, no, no.
Not quite all the way
to feelings. More like...

1225
01:31:09.000 --> 01:31:10.800
All right,
feelings, damn you.

1226
01:31:10.920 --> 01:31:15.120
And you left her still.
Ooh, that's low.

1227
01:31:16.960 --> 01:31:18.280
Thank you.

1228
01:31:19.360 --> 01:31:21.280
[branch snaps]
Shh!

1229
01:31:25.200 --> 01:31:26.560
Stealth over force.

1230
01:31:26.640 --> 01:31:30.000
I'll take it from here
on account of your condition.

1231
01:31:31.200 --> 01:31:33.040
You don't have
termites, do you?

1232
01:31:33.240 --> 01:31:35.680
I appreciate
your concern, Jack,

1233
01:31:35.760 --> 01:31:38.040
but I'll be keeping
you company all the same.

1234
01:31:38.280 --> 01:31:41.440
Hold here,
Lieutenant Commander.
Wait for my signal.

1235
01:31:55.640 --> 01:31:57.840
[indistinct chattering]

1236
01:32:11.520 --> 01:32:13.240
[indistinct chatter]

1237
01:32:13.320 --> 01:32:15.600
[Barbossa] There. That one.
That be the leader.

1238
01:32:15.760 --> 01:32:18.440
Make note of his tent
because that's where...

1239
01:32:19.160 --> 01:32:23.360
No, wait. By God,
that must be them
right there.

1240
01:32:26.160 --> 01:32:29.760
[sniffing]
Your sword smells funny.

1241
01:32:29.840 --> 01:32:34.600
Aye. Poison from the
innards of poisonous toads.

1242
01:32:34.760 --> 01:32:38.080
Just a scratch,
you're a dead man in minutes.

1243
01:32:38.240 --> 01:32:40.240
Would you mind pointing it
the other way?

1244
01:32:40.320 --> 01:32:41.680
I don't like toads.

1245
01:32:47.120 --> 01:32:48.400
What are you doing?

1246
01:32:48.480 --> 01:32:50.640
Planning an escape route.

1247
01:32:50.720 --> 01:32:52.320
Isn't that how you do it?

1248
01:32:53.280 --> 01:32:54.920
Yes.

1249
01:32:55.000 --> 01:32:58.240
Or sometimes I just...
improvise.

1250
01:33:25.040 --> 01:33:26.440
Now what?

1251
01:33:26.880 --> 01:33:29.920
We stroll out,
slow and steady.

1252
01:33:30.000 --> 01:33:31.720
Just like we belong.

1253
01:33:42.880 --> 01:33:44.920
[all grunting]
[swords clanging]

1254
01:34:05.520 --> 01:34:07.560
[guns cocking]

1255
01:34:13.760 --> 01:34:15.920
[groaning]

1256
01:34:25.280 --> 01:34:27.600
[animal chirping nearby]

1257
01:34:27.840 --> 01:34:29.120
[footsteps approaching]

1258
01:34:29.200 --> 01:34:32.800
[panting] I'm sorry, Syrena.

1259
01:34:33.760 --> 01:34:35.920
Philip, you're alive.

1260
01:34:36.160 --> 01:34:37.120
Yes.

1261
01:34:37.840 --> 01:34:39.360
You came for me.

1262
01:34:41.640 --> 01:34:42.880
Why?

1263
01:34:45.360 --> 01:34:47.720
You're different,
are you not?

1264
01:34:50.000 --> 01:34:53.600
Do you know not of kindness?
Compassion?

1265
01:34:59.280 --> 01:35:01.240
[grunting, yelling]

1266
01:35:11.360 --> 01:35:13.280
Tears of sorrow, never.

1267
01:35:13.360 --> 01:35:15.800
Mermaids be
too tough for that.

1268
01:35:15.920 --> 01:35:17.880
But tears of joy...

1269
01:35:19.640 --> 01:35:22.400
They say these be
the more potent anyway.

1270
01:35:22.520 --> 01:35:24.720
Syrena, on my word,
I had no part in this.

1271
01:35:26.520 --> 01:35:28.080
Let her go.
You don't need her now.

1272
01:35:28.160 --> 01:35:31.080
Let her go? No.

1273
01:35:31.160 --> 01:35:34.000
Secure her bonds.
We leave her with her own.

1274
01:35:43.600 --> 01:35:46.200
[Jack] How's that
escape route working?

1275
01:35:46.280 --> 01:35:48.400
Here's your chance
to improvise.

1276
01:35:49.000 --> 01:35:50.560
I'm attempting it.

1277
01:35:50.680 --> 01:35:53.360
I might be able to get
a hand loose.

1278
01:35:53.440 --> 01:35:55.800
Oh, you got a knife.
That's very good.

1279
01:35:56.800 --> 01:35:58.040
Better.

1280
01:36:00.040 --> 01:36:01.680
[liquid sloshing]

1281
01:36:03.720 --> 01:36:05.120
I want one of those.

1282
01:36:09.760 --> 01:36:13.480
Here's to revenge.
Sweet and clear.

1283
01:36:14.320 --> 01:36:15.800
Revenge?

1284
01:36:16.440 --> 01:36:18.120
Come, come, Hector.

1285
01:36:18.200 --> 01:36:20.120
If you wanted
the chalices,

1286
01:36:20.200 --> 01:36:22.200
you'd seen they were
missing and gone.

1287
01:36:22.800 --> 01:36:26.320
You were lying in wait,
for Blackbeard.

1288
01:36:27.080 --> 01:36:28.320
Oh?

1289
01:36:28.400 --> 01:36:31.520
King George.
Privateer. Wig.

1290
01:36:32.720 --> 01:36:35.160
Cheap theatrical facade.
I'm not buying it.

1291
01:36:35.280 --> 01:36:37.240
You weren't there that night.

1292
01:36:37.360 --> 01:36:38.720
When the <i>Pearl</i> was lost?

1293
01:36:38.840 --> 01:36:41.280
Taken, not lost.

1294
01:36:43.400 --> 01:36:45.320
We were off the coast
of Hispaniola when

1295
01:36:45.400 --> 01:36:47.800
we came under attack.
<i>[ship creaking]</i>

1296
01:36:47.880 --> 01:36:51.200
No provocation nor warning
nor offer of parley.

1297
01:36:51.520 --> 01:36:54.080
We were peppered
with cannon fire.

1298
01:36:54.160 --> 01:36:55.280
<i>[shots firing]</i>

1299
01:36:55.360 --> 01:36:58.520
And then the sea beneath
the <i>Pearl</i> began to roil.

1300
01:36:58.600 --> 01:37:00.160
<i>[sea roiling]</i>

1301
01:37:00.240 --> 01:37:02.680
The <i>Pearl</i> was pitching
and yawing violently.

1302
01:37:02.800 --> 01:37:04.400
Every plank, every rail,

1303
01:37:04.480 --> 01:37:07.520
every spar, all at once,
began to creak.

1304
01:37:07.840 --> 01:37:10.440
The rigging had come to life.
<i>[ship creaking]</i>

1305
01:37:10.520 --> 01:37:13.280
Our own ship
turned against us...

1306
01:37:13.760 --> 01:37:16.920
...tangling the crew,
wrapping around 'em
like snakes.

1307
01:37:17.000 --> 01:37:19.000
And wrapping around me leg.

1308
01:37:19.440 --> 01:37:22.200
But me arms were free
and me sword was to hand.

1309
01:37:22.320 --> 01:37:25.440
I am the master of me ship,
not Blackbeard.

1310
01:37:26.040 --> 01:37:29.520
I am the master of my fate,
not Blackbeard.

1311
01:37:30.160 --> 01:37:33.040
So I did what needed done.

1312
01:37:39.480 --> 01:37:41.520
I survived.

1313
01:37:43.040 --> 01:37:47.440
So... you're not
after the Fountain.

1314
01:37:47.560 --> 01:37:51.240
I care not for King George
or tavern yarns

1315
01:37:51.320 --> 01:37:53.480
that give hope
for a healed limb.

1316
01:37:54.800 --> 01:37:58.920
But I'd give my left arm
for a chance at Blackbeard.

1317
01:37:59.200 --> 01:38:01.960
Not your right?
I need me good arm

1318
01:38:02.040 --> 01:38:06.800
to drive my poisoned blade
through his heart.

1319
01:38:07.600 --> 01:38:10.160
I'll see you get
the chance, mate.

1320
01:38:23.640 --> 01:38:25.840
[soft grunting]

1321
01:38:33.840 --> 01:38:36.640
[indistinct chatter
in Spanish]

1322
01:38:54.440 --> 01:38:56.680
[tree creaking]
[wind whistling]

1323
01:39:16.560 --> 01:39:18.160
[creaking]

1324
01:39:28.720 --> 01:39:30.240
The prisoner's escaping.

1325
01:39:36.000 --> 01:39:36.920
[grunting]

1326
01:39:37.640 --> 01:39:40.360
He's escaping!
Fan out! Find him!

1327
01:39:40.480 --> 01:39:43.360
Go! Go!
[gunfire]

1328
01:39:43.440 --> 01:39:46.680
Hold your fire!
I want him alive!

1329
01:39:47.640 --> 01:39:50.280
[shouting in Spanish]

1330
01:39:54.240 --> 01:39:56.360
I figured
that was the signal.

1331
01:40:13.520 --> 01:40:15.800
[men yelling]

1332
01:40:22.840 --> 01:40:24.160
[men shouting]

1333
01:40:33.520 --> 01:40:35.760
[men shouting in Spanish]

1334
01:40:39.520 --> 01:40:41.240
Go! Prepare to move out!

1335
01:40:41.320 --> 01:40:42.800
The enemy is soon upon us.

1336
01:40:44.840 --> 01:40:46.480
I'm sorry about
the chalices, Jack,

1337
01:40:46.560 --> 01:40:47.840
but I've an
appointment to keep.

1338
01:40:47.920 --> 01:40:49.120
I'll not be going back.

1339
01:40:49.240 --> 01:40:50.440
No need.

1340
01:40:51.280 --> 01:40:52.440
Shall we have a drink?

1341
01:40:52.520 --> 01:40:54.040
We'll drink at the Fountain.

1342
01:41:05.080 --> 01:41:07.520
[birds chirping]

1343
01:41:10.760 --> 01:41:12.480
[gasps]

1344
01:41:13.000 --> 01:41:14.480
How is it we can never meet

1345
01:41:14.560 --> 01:41:16.560
without you pointing
something at me?

1346
01:41:16.920 --> 01:41:19.280
You brought the chalices,
Sparrow?

1347
01:41:19.400 --> 01:41:21.600
Aye. Oi!

1348
01:41:22.040 --> 01:41:25.280
[pig oinking]

1349
01:41:25.360 --> 01:41:28.080
[Angelica] I see you
brought a friend.
[Jack] I did.

1350
01:41:28.160 --> 01:41:32.000
And the one-legged man,
he is near. Aye?

1351
01:41:32.120 --> 01:41:33.080
Aye.

1352
01:41:34.360 --> 01:41:37.000
Now... Before I go
just handing them over,

1353
01:41:37.080 --> 01:41:38.400
I do have one
or two conditions.

1354
01:41:38.480 --> 01:41:40.080
Name them.
Firstly,

1355
01:41:40.200 --> 01:41:41.920
I'll be having
me compass back.

1356
01:41:42.000 --> 01:41:43.360
No, no,
that's secondly.

1357
01:41:43.440 --> 01:41:45.360
Firstly, upon your word,

1358
01:41:45.440 --> 01:41:47.560
you will bring
no harm to Angelica.

1359
01:41:47.680 --> 01:41:50.080
[Blackbeard] I'll make
no vows to the likes
of you, Sparrow.

1360
01:41:50.480 --> 01:41:53.120
But it costs me
nothing to admit

1361
01:41:53.200 --> 01:41:55.560
that she was never
in harm's way.

1362
01:41:56.080 --> 01:41:58.160
Secondly then,
priorly firstly,

1363
01:41:58.240 --> 01:42:00.160
I will be having
me compass back.

1364
01:42:00.800 --> 01:42:03.120
Please? I do deserve it.

1365
01:42:03.200 --> 01:42:04.840
Do you have any idea
how difficult it was

1366
01:42:04.920 --> 01:42:06.200
to catch that filthy pig?

1367
01:42:06.320 --> 01:42:09.200
Not the big one,
the four-legged one.

1368
01:42:12.160 --> 01:42:16.560
Thank you.
And thirdly, Mr. Beard,

1369
01:42:17.080 --> 01:42:19.400
there are times,
not very often,

1370
01:42:19.520 --> 01:42:22.640
when I do reflect
upon my heinous misdeeds.

1371
01:42:22.760 --> 01:42:27.040
Chief among them,
I note how poorly I have
treated Mr. Gibbs,

1372
01:42:27.120 --> 01:42:28.320
my loyal first mate.

1373
01:42:28.400 --> 01:42:30.280
Aye! Now you bring it up...

1374
01:42:30.360 --> 01:42:32.680
Left him to rot in jail,
I did. Didn't care.

1375
01:42:32.800 --> 01:42:37.160
Still don't. But, point being,
you must let him go free.

1376
01:42:39.040 --> 01:42:40.240
Is that it?

1377
01:42:41.120 --> 01:42:42.320
I think so.

1378
01:42:42.840 --> 01:42:45.400
Quick, or the pig runs,
and good luck getting
those chalices.

1379
01:42:45.480 --> 01:42:47.040
Jack, if it's all the same
to you, I'd be just as...

1380
01:42:47.160 --> 01:42:47.880
Done.

1381
01:42:48.000 --> 01:42:49.760
Release the swine.

1382
01:42:49.840 --> 01:42:51.080
[squealing]

1383
01:42:55.640 --> 01:42:57.000
Perhaps, if you don't mind,

1384
01:42:57.080 --> 01:42:59.160
I could tag along
with you folk for a...

1385
01:43:01.360 --> 01:43:03.920
This will lead you
to freedom, mate.

1386
01:43:10.560 --> 01:43:13.120
I could have swore it was
somewhere right around here.

1387
01:44:39.200 --> 01:44:41.320
[crackling]

1388
01:44:43.360 --> 01:44:45.160
We must not stop.

1389
01:45:02.160 --> 01:45:04.880
Aha! Dead end.

1390
01:45:05.320 --> 01:45:07.520
Dead. End.

1391
01:45:08.040 --> 01:45:09.600
[Jack] Dead end.

1392
01:45:10.520 --> 01:45:11.920
Jack, I'm starting to think

1393
01:45:12.000 --> 01:45:13.600
you don't know
where you're going.

1394
01:45:14.240 --> 01:45:17.200
It is not the destination
so much as the journey,
they say.

1395
01:45:18.520 --> 01:45:20.240
Chalices, if you please.

1396
01:45:32.040 --> 01:45:33.360
Stand back.

1397
01:45:43.080 --> 01:45:47.440
[chalices clinking,
tone echoing]

1398
01:45:52.600 --> 01:45:55.120
[chalices clinking,
tone echoing]

1399
01:45:55.200 --> 01:45:57.480
[clears throat]
Jack...

1400
01:45:57.600 --> 01:45:59.480
...have you ever, in fact...

1401
01:45:59.600 --> 01:46:05.200
...seen with
your own eyes...
the Fountain of Youth?

1402
01:46:05.320 --> 01:46:07.840
I'm sorry, could you repeat
the question, please?

1403
01:46:07.920 --> 01:46:09.080
Quartermaster.

1404
01:46:09.200 --> 01:46:10.920
[gun cocking]
No, no!

1405
01:46:11.040 --> 01:46:12.960
[firing, bullet ricocheting]

1406
01:46:13.080 --> 01:46:16.800
[gun cocking]
Wait, wait! Wait.

1407
01:46:20.120 --> 01:46:23.600
<i>"Aqua... de Vida."</i>

1408
01:46:24.120 --> 01:46:27.280
[low rumbling]

1409
01:47:03.840 --> 01:47:05.160
Master Scrum...

1410
01:47:06.320 --> 01:47:07.800
...do you mind?

1411
01:47:07.880 --> 01:47:09.160
Squire?

1412
01:47:25.560 --> 01:47:27.360
[grunting]

1413
01:47:42.560 --> 01:47:45.240
[birds chirping]

1414
01:48:08.160 --> 01:48:10.160
So beautiful.

1415
01:48:49.560 --> 01:48:53.120
Sparrow, I'll be the first
to taste those waters.

1416
01:48:56.480 --> 01:48:57.920
Father.

1417
01:49:01.280 --> 01:49:03.040
The one-legged man.

1418
01:49:06.160 --> 01:49:07.560
You brought him here.

1419
01:49:08.280 --> 01:49:09.960
Would I do that?

1420
01:49:10.040 --> 01:49:12.360
[Barbossa] Edward Teach!

1421
01:49:12.800 --> 01:49:15.680
For crimes committed
on the high seas,

1422
01:49:15.760 --> 01:49:19.680
by the authority granted me
by His Majesty the King...

1423
01:49:19.760 --> 01:49:23.160
...and with a goodly amount
of personal satisfaction...

1424
01:49:23.240 --> 01:49:26.440
...I hereby place you
in the custody of the court,

1425
01:49:26.520 --> 01:49:30.000
and declare you
to be my prisoner.

1426
01:49:30.880 --> 01:49:34.520
My trick's out, is that it?

1427
01:49:34.600 --> 01:49:39.760
Such crimes do include,
but are not limited to,
piracy, treason,

1428
01:49:39.840 --> 01:49:43.280
murder, torture of
the most heinous sort,

1429
01:49:43.360 --> 01:49:45.880
including the brutal theft
of one used,

1430
01:49:45.960 --> 01:49:47.920
twisted, hairy right leg.

1431
01:49:48.000 --> 01:49:53.080
You... dare face
this sword?

1432
01:49:53.200 --> 01:49:55.680
This far away
from your ship? Aye.

1433
01:49:55.800 --> 01:50:00.440
Aye. That be the cold breath
of fate I feel down my nape.

1434
01:50:00.520 --> 01:50:06.280
But I'll have
one last fight, by God.

1435
01:50:06.360 --> 01:50:07.520
Kill 'em all!
[men yelling]

1436
01:50:07.640 --> 01:50:11.640
Whoa, whoa!
Hang on a minute.

1437
01:50:12.120 --> 01:50:15.040
I just... I just need
to understand something.

1438
01:50:15.440 --> 01:50:19.160
Right, so, you will
fight against them,

1439
01:50:19.240 --> 01:50:20.840
they will fight
against you.

1440
01:50:20.920 --> 01:50:23.440
All on account of him
wanting to kill him?

1441
01:50:24.640 --> 01:50:26.480
Where is the sense?

1442
01:50:26.800 --> 01:50:28.400
Exactly.

1443
01:50:28.520 --> 01:50:32.280
I say, let them fight
each other while we lay back,

1444
01:50:32.400 --> 01:50:35.960
watch, have a drink,
place some wagers! Eh?

1445
01:50:36.080 --> 01:50:38.400
Hmm. Aye.

1446
01:50:40.920 --> 01:50:42.480
Kill 'em!
No quarter!

1447
01:50:42.600 --> 01:50:44.760
[men shouting]
[swords clanging]

1448
01:50:44.880 --> 01:50:46.560
[gunfire]

1449
01:51:12.120 --> 01:51:14.600
[groaning]
Get off me!

1450
01:51:37.880 --> 01:51:40.800
[shouting continues]
[swords clanging]

1451
01:51:45.120 --> 01:51:47.520
[Angelica grunting]

1452
01:51:47.640 --> 01:51:49.080
Scrum, the chalices!

1453
01:51:50.920 --> 01:51:52.520
And the tear! Follow!

1454
01:51:56.040 --> 01:51:57.040
[Blackbeard] Fight!

1455
01:51:58.120 --> 01:52:00.680
Hand it over. The tear.

1456
01:52:00.760 --> 01:52:01.960
There's a good lad.

1457
01:52:02.400 --> 01:52:03.920
I'm more afraid of her
than I am of you.

1458
01:52:07.120 --> 01:52:09.360
[grunting]

1459
01:52:09.440 --> 01:52:12.000
Hand it over.
There's a good lad.

1460
01:52:15.600 --> 01:52:17.320
The chalices, if you please.

1461
01:52:17.440 --> 01:52:19.360
[chuckles] Sorry, Jack.

1462
01:52:19.440 --> 01:52:23.520
I told you, I need years.
And now, yours will do.

1463
01:52:28.160 --> 01:52:29.320
Aha!

1464
01:52:31.520 --> 01:52:32.800
Scrum!

1465
01:52:52.000 --> 01:52:54.320
[panting]

1466
01:52:54.400 --> 01:52:55.800
Syrena...

1467
01:52:59.560 --> 01:53:02.400
My God, you will
not take her.

1468
01:53:02.520 --> 01:53:06.640
If you have taken her,
you will give her back.

1469
01:53:07.080 --> 01:53:10.000
Give her back...
[panting]

1470
01:53:10.360 --> 01:53:12.800
[whispers] Give her back,
please. Please.

1471
01:53:24.800 --> 01:53:25.960
[swords clanging]

1472
01:53:26.080 --> 01:53:27.560
[both grunting]

1473
01:53:30.240 --> 01:53:32.560
[growling]
[grunting]

1474
01:53:34.960 --> 01:53:39.240
[chuckles] I expected
fate to put up more
of a fight, eh?

1475
01:53:39.360 --> 01:53:40.680
[grunting]

1476
01:53:40.800 --> 01:53:42.080
[shouting]

1477
01:53:49.920 --> 01:53:51.480
[yelling]

1478
01:53:55.800 --> 01:53:59.840
I will not have that smile
on your face as I strike
you down.

1479
01:54:01.200 --> 01:54:04.600
Take a gander, Edward Teach.

1480
01:54:34.840 --> 01:54:38.160
This land is hereby forever
claimed in the glorious name

1481
01:54:38.240 --> 01:54:40.040
of His Majesty
King George... [grunts]

1482
01:54:40.120 --> 01:54:41.440
[gunshot]

1483
01:54:47.320 --> 01:54:49.920
Someone make a note
of that man's bravery.

1484
01:54:57.360 --> 01:55:00.560
<i>Senorita,</i> the chalices,
<i>por favor.</i>

1485
01:55:17.520 --> 01:55:23.360
Only God
can grant eternal life,
not this pagan water.

1486
01:55:23.600 --> 01:55:24.720
[chalices clattering]

1487
01:55:34.400 --> 01:55:37.520
Men, destroy this
profane temple!

1488
01:55:37.600 --> 01:55:40.480
[men shouting]

1489
01:55:40.600 --> 01:55:41.840
The Fountain!

1490
01:55:56.200 --> 01:55:57.520
You are a fool.

1491
01:55:57.880 --> 01:56:00.800
You seek in this place
what only faith can provide.

1492
01:56:00.880 --> 01:56:03.440
Faith? In faith,
there is light enough to see

1493
01:56:03.560 --> 01:56:05.920
but darkness enough to blind.

1494
01:56:09.600 --> 01:56:11.800
What devilry is this?

1495
01:56:11.880 --> 01:56:13.960
[gasps]

1496
01:56:15.760 --> 01:56:17.400
For the <i>Pearl.</i>

1497
01:56:17.520 --> 01:56:19.160
What have you done?

1498
01:56:20.000 --> 01:56:21.120
[grunting]

1499
01:56:21.840 --> 01:56:24.280
Angelica! Don't!
It's poison!

1500
01:56:25.280 --> 01:56:26.320
[gasps]

1501
01:56:28.480 --> 01:56:31.360
[Barbossa]
I'm not such the fool
to take on Blackbeard

1502
01:56:31.480 --> 01:56:34.800
without a little
venomous advantage.

1503
01:56:36.160 --> 01:56:37.200
Jack!

1504
01:56:38.240 --> 01:56:40.320
[men yelling]

1505
01:56:49.440 --> 01:56:51.600
I claim Blackbeard's
ship and crew,

1506
01:56:51.720 --> 01:56:55.320
and this sword,
payment for my missing limb!

1507
01:56:55.400 --> 01:56:56.440
[rock crumbling]

1508
01:57:09.000 --> 01:57:11.600
[man] Hang on! Pull!
[grunting]

1509
01:57:35.360 --> 01:57:37.760
[speaks Spanish]

1510
01:57:56.360 --> 01:57:58.920
Do not waste my tear.

1511
01:58:03.600 --> 01:58:04.680
[gasping]

1512
01:58:27.920 --> 01:58:30.000
Drink this.
This one has the tear.

1513
01:58:30.080 --> 01:58:32.280
You must drink the other.
No!

1514
01:58:33.240 --> 01:58:36.200
I cannot save you both.
One of you must sacrifice.

1515
01:58:37.120 --> 01:58:41.280
You take it, Father,
for your soul.

1516
01:58:42.120 --> 01:58:47.120
Captain Teach, she's dying.
You must save your daughter.

1517
01:58:49.120 --> 01:58:51.000
This one takes life?

1518
01:58:51.480 --> 01:58:53.840
This one has the tear
and gives life?

1519
01:58:53.960 --> 01:58:55.280
Aye, hurry!

1520
01:59:03.880 --> 01:59:08.200
Angelica...
Save me, my child.

1521
01:59:10.320 --> 01:59:11.200
No.

1522
01:59:15.320 --> 01:59:16.520
[gasping]

1523
01:59:20.240 --> 01:59:21.840
I love you, Father.

1524
01:59:34.840 --> 01:59:36.000
Wait a minute.

1525
01:59:38.760 --> 01:59:41.400
In fact, it might have been
the other way around.

1526
01:59:42.560 --> 01:59:45.960
This cup had the tear,
that one had the other bit.

1527
01:59:46.400 --> 01:59:47.560
[Blackbeard] Trickster!
Hmm?

1528
01:59:47.680 --> 01:59:49.400
Devil!
Father!

1529
01:59:56.320 --> 01:59:58.800
You bastard!
How could you?

1530
01:59:58.960 --> 02:00:00.600
Your father saved you.

1531
02:00:00.720 --> 02:00:03.120
Perhaps his soul
is now redeemed. Eh?

1532
02:00:03.760 --> 02:00:06.000
[rumbling]

1533
02:00:16.080 --> 02:00:18.800
[wind whistling]

1534
02:00:49.080 --> 02:00:52.320
[gasping, panting]

1535
02:01:03.840 --> 02:01:05.280
You are hurt.

1536
02:01:08.000 --> 02:01:09.840
In body only.

1537
02:01:11.840 --> 02:01:16.200
My mind is at peace...
because of you.

1538
02:01:17.040 --> 02:01:18.080
Me?

1539
02:01:18.800 --> 02:01:19.920
Yes.

1540
02:01:20.880 --> 02:01:22.480
I was lost.

1541
02:01:24.400 --> 02:01:27.960
The wind, the tides...

1542
02:01:29.160 --> 02:01:31.360
...they ought to
renew a man's faith.

1543
02:01:34.000 --> 02:01:35.640
But for me, only you.

1544
02:01:37.080 --> 02:01:39.960
Philip, I can save you.

1545
02:01:40.560 --> 02:01:42.920
You need only ask.

1546
02:01:44.840 --> 02:01:47.640
I seek but one thing.

1547
02:01:47.960 --> 02:01:49.480
What is that?

1548
02:01:50.720 --> 02:01:52.280
Forgiveness.

1549
02:01:53.040 --> 02:01:55.760
If not for me, you would
never have been captured.

1550
02:01:56.640 --> 02:01:58.000
[whispers] Ask.

1551
02:02:00.320 --> 02:02:01.840
Forgive me?

1552
02:02:27.200 --> 02:02:28.600
I hate you.

1553
02:02:28.720 --> 02:02:30.840
The bloke
who saved your life?

1554
02:02:30.920 --> 02:02:34.440
The years I possess,
stolen from my own father!

1555
02:02:34.520 --> 02:02:37.560
I only helped Blackbeard
do what any father
should have done.

1556
02:02:38.040 --> 02:02:40.760
You are cruel and ignorant.

1557
02:02:43.320 --> 02:02:44.480
[yelling]

1558
02:02:44.960 --> 02:02:47.120
One pistol, one shot.

1559
02:02:47.200 --> 02:02:48.720
[gasps]

1560
02:02:48.800 --> 02:02:50.520
To kill myself
before I starve?

1561
02:02:50.760 --> 02:02:52.280
[Jack] There's no
trusting you, love.

1562
02:02:52.360 --> 02:02:54.920
Besides, this is
a well-traveled trade route.

1563
02:02:55.000 --> 02:02:56.760
You can signal a passing ship.

1564
02:02:57.040 --> 02:03:00.160
Or you can just
bite the proverbial
bullet, as it were.

1565
02:03:00.560 --> 02:03:02.760
And how will I get free
of these bonds?

1566
02:03:02.840 --> 02:03:04.880
You broke free of your bonds
half an hour ago,

1567
02:03:04.960 --> 02:03:07.400
waiting for the precise
moment to pounce.

1568
02:03:10.680 --> 02:03:12.080
Admit it, Jack.

1569
02:03:12.200 --> 02:03:13.760
You still love me.

1570
02:03:14.480 --> 02:03:16.400
If you had a sister
and a dog,

1571
02:03:16.480 --> 02:03:18.480
I'd choose the dog.

1572
02:03:19.440 --> 02:03:22.600
Treasure! There is
a chest with jewels!

1573
02:03:22.680 --> 02:03:24.920
Jewels with the power
to rule the wind and tide!

1574
02:03:25.000 --> 02:03:26.120
You're making that up!

1575
02:03:26.200 --> 02:03:29.160
Wait... [panting]

1576
02:03:29.240 --> 02:03:32.400
I am with child. Yours.

1577
02:03:33.600 --> 02:03:35.160
I don't recall
that we ever had...

1578
02:03:35.280 --> 02:03:36.120
You were drunk!

1579
02:03:36.240 --> 02:03:38.040
I've actually
never been that drunk.

1580
02:03:38.160 --> 02:03:39.400
Wait!

1581
02:03:40.680 --> 02:03:43.240
There is something
I want to say to you.

1582
02:03:43.680 --> 02:03:47.520
Something I wanted to say
from the moment we first met.

1583
02:03:48.240 --> 02:03:49.640
Go on, then.

1584
02:03:51.760 --> 02:03:53.400
I love you.

1585
02:03:56.720 --> 02:03:58.280
As do I.

1586
02:03:58.640 --> 02:04:02.400
Always have.
Always will.

1587
02:04:06.640 --> 02:04:08.120
I gotta go.

1588
02:04:08.200 --> 02:04:09.360
Jack!

1589
02:04:11.520 --> 02:04:13.320
This is not over!

1590
02:04:14.160 --> 02:04:15.440
Jack!

1591
02:04:22.240 --> 02:04:24.120
[gunshot]
[water splashes]

1592
02:04:25.000 --> 02:04:26.240
Missed!

1593
02:04:26.640 --> 02:04:29.920
[Angelica screaming
in Spanish]

1594
02:04:41.880 --> 02:04:44.720
The <i>Revenge</i> is mine.

1595
02:04:51.360 --> 02:04:52.960
Sir...

1596
02:04:55.520 --> 02:04:57.400
We found this
below decks.

1597
02:05:05.280 --> 02:05:06.960
[sword vibrating]

1598
02:05:17.400 --> 02:05:18.960
[men yelling]

1599
02:05:23.760 --> 02:05:25.920
All hands!
Ply to windward!

1600
02:05:26.040 --> 02:05:28.960
Get cracking,
ye blooming cockroaches!

1601
02:05:29.040 --> 02:05:32.080
[cackling]
[all laughing]

1602
02:05:32.160 --> 02:05:34.960
The Crown served me well.

1603
02:05:35.040 --> 02:05:37.720
But now, by the gods
of sea and sky...

1604
02:05:37.800 --> 02:05:41.520
...make way for Tortuga!

1605
02:05:41.600 --> 02:05:43.560
[men shouting]

1606
02:05:53.520 --> 02:05:56.280
Gibbs, you filthy, besotted
shellback, you made it!

1607
02:05:56.360 --> 02:05:57.720
[Gibbs] Aye!

1608
02:05:57.800 --> 02:05:59.720
And I trust
we managed a profit

1609
02:05:59.800 --> 02:06:01.640
from our joint enterprise?

1610
02:06:01.840 --> 02:06:04.120
Feast your eyes.

1611
02:06:08.760 --> 02:06:11.680
The compass led me
straight and true.

1612
02:06:11.760 --> 02:06:13.960
What of Blackbeard's men
guarding the ship?

1613
02:06:14.040 --> 02:06:17.280
I employed the selfsame
maneuver we perfected
in New Guinea.

1614
02:06:17.360 --> 02:06:18.000
Oh.

1615
02:06:18.080 --> 02:06:21.800
Seemed a shame to leave
an entire fleet behind.

1616
02:06:22.280 --> 02:06:24.400
Shame indeed.
[chuckles]

1617
02:06:32.640 --> 02:06:35.080
[bird squawking]
[squealing]

1618
02:06:36.240 --> 02:06:37.520
I hate that monkey.

1619
02:06:37.600 --> 02:06:38.640
So, the <i>Pearl...</i>

1620
02:06:38.720 --> 02:06:40.800
Any idea how
to get her out?

1621
02:06:40.880 --> 02:06:44.240
We shall need a crossbow,
an hourglass, three goats.

1622
02:06:44.320 --> 02:06:47.560
One of us must learn to
play the trumpet whilst the
other one goes like this...

1623
02:06:47.640 --> 02:06:49.120
I know a man with a goat.

1624
02:06:49.280 --> 02:06:51.280
Good. I can go like this.

1625
02:06:53.840 --> 02:06:55.600
[Gibbs] Jack,
I have to ask...

1626
02:06:55.680 --> 02:06:58.320
You had the chalices,
the water, the tear...

1627
02:06:58.400 --> 02:07:01.400
You could have lived
maybe forever.

1628
02:07:01.480 --> 02:07:03.280
[Jack] The Fountain
does test you, Gibbs.

1629
02:07:03.360 --> 02:07:06.040
But better to not know
which moment may be your last.

1630
02:07:06.120 --> 02:07:08.520
Every morsel
of your entire being

1631
02:07:08.600 --> 02:07:11.520
alive to the infinite
mystery of it all.

1632
02:07:11.600 --> 02:07:14.400
And who's to say
I won't live forever, eh?

1633
02:07:14.680 --> 02:07:18.240
Discoverer of the
Fountain of Youth.
[chuckling]

1634
02:07:18.360 --> 02:07:20.880
[Jack] I have
no say in it, Gibbs.

1635
02:07:20.960 --> 02:07:22.880
It's a pirate's life for me.

1636
02:07:23.920 --> 02:07:25.280
Savvy?

1637
02:15:37.680 --> 02:15:39.480
[gulls crying]

1638
02:16:02.960 --> 02:16:04.800
[thunder rumbling]

1639
02:16:08.080 --> 02:16:10.120
[thunder cracks]

